New Records: Victor Wembanyama scored a career-high 50 points
Wembanyama is the first player in league history with 20 3-pointers and 25 blocks over a six-game span
Key Match Events: Wembanyama made an 18-foot jumper for his 49th and 50th points with 8:49 remaining to give San Antonio a 115-98 lead
Post-Match Reflections: The coach highlighted the victory as a crucial step toward the championship
Miscellaneous Highlights: Alexandre Sarr blocked Wembanya's shot in the second quarter and dunked on his fellow Frenchman in the third quarter
